## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="7e0c1-102">Le code c# suivant montre comment utiliser le Gestionnaire d’événements.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7e0c1-102">The following C# code shows how to use the event handler.</span></span>  

```csharp  
//Add a new event handler.  
XmlDocument doc = new XmlDocument();  
doc.NodeInserted += new XmlNodeChangedEventHandler(NodeInsertedHandler);  
//Define the event handler.  
void NodeInsertedHandler(Object src, XmlNodeChangedEventArgs args)  
{  
 Console.WriteLine("Node " + args.Node.Name + " inserted!!");  
}  
```  

> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="7e0c1-103">Si une opération se compose de plusieurs actions, il en résulte plusieurs événements.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7e0c1-103">If an operation is comprised of multiple actions, it results in multiple events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7e0c1-104">Par exemple, un <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode.AppendChild%2A> un appel peut avoir supprimer le nœud ajouté de son parent précédent.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7e0c1-104">For example, an <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode.AppendChild%2A> call may have to remove the node being appended from its previous parent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7e0c1-105">Dans ce cas, vous verrez un `NodeRemoved` événement suivi par un `NodeInserted` événement.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7e0c1-105">In this case you will see a `NodeRemoved` event followed by a `NodeInserted` event.</span></span>
